[SN]TITLE[SN]
Doncaster man admits sexually abusing seven boys

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has pleaded guilty to sexually abusing boys as young as six over a four-year period.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
David Jamfrey, 60, of Middlegate, in Scawthorpe, Doncaster, "deliberately targeted and groomed" seven boys between January 2010 and May 2014.
Jamfrey pleaded guilty at Sheffield Crown Court to 17 sexual offences. He will be sentenced on July 16.
Det Con David Whitehouse said he was pleased Jamfrey had admitted his "sick crimes".
He said: "Jamfrey is a dangerous man who deliberately targeted and groomed vulnerable young boys for his own sexual gratification."
Jamfrey pleaded guilty to 11 counts of sexual assault of a male under 13 and four counts of sexual activity with a male aged between 13 and 15.
He also admitted one count of engaging in sexual activity in the presence of a child under 16 and one count of attempting to engage in sexual activity with a child.
His victims were aged between six and 15.
